Automatic trial exclusion

## TEMP:
# included_trials = c(55, 85, 87, 120)
# samples = samples[samples$trial %in% included_trials,]
# trials = trials[trials$trial %in% included_trials,]
# blanks = blanks[blanks$trial %in% included_trials,]
if(cond %in% c('cond-v', 'cond-m')){
  # Excluding trials with no blink:
  excl_no_blink = data.frame(trial = trials$trial[!trials$trial %in% blanks$trial],
                             excl_reason = 'no blink')
  # samples = samples[samples$trial!=excl_no_blink,]
  # trials = trials[trials$trial!=excl_no_blink,]
} else {
  excl_no_blink = NULL
}
if(cond!='cond-m'){
  # Excluding trials with target blinks (blinks during target presentation):
  merged = merge(trials[,c('trial','resp_time','trial_time_beg')],
                 blanks[,c('trial','blank_time_end')], by='trial')
  merged$rt = with(merged, resp_time - trial_time_beg)
  excl_targ_blink = data.frame(trial = unique(merged$trial[merged$blank_time_end>
                                                             (merged$rt+eo_tolerance)]),
                               excl_reason = 'target blink')
  # samples = samples[samples$trial!=excl_targ_blink,]
  # trials = trials[trials$trial!=excl_targ_blink,]
} else {
  excl_targ_blink = NULL
}
# Excluding trials with noisy data:

# Printing all exclusions to screen
( all_excl = rbind(excl_targ_blink, excl_no_blink) )
